node.text:
10 years ago, Occupy Wall Street transformed American politics.

-Scrutiny of wealth inequality.
-Wide support for taxing the rich.
-Bernie’s meteoric rise.

There is plenty we can learn from Occupy's missteps, but the movement had more impact than you think.

node.title: 10 Years Since Occupy: What Did We Learn?

node.text:
10 years ago, Occupy Wall Street transformed American politics.

-Scrutiny of wealth inequality.
-Wide support for taxing the rich.
-Bernie’s meteoric rise.

There is plenty we can learn from Occupy's missteps, but the movement had more impact than you think.

All should be primaried by people who care more about advancing the public good than protecting private profits.

node.text: Yesterday, Democrats on the House Ways and Means Committee released a tax plan that targets income and not wealth — even though the richest 0.01% have as much wealth as the bottom 90%. Why leave such vast fortunes unscathed? Answer: Corporate lobbyists and campaign contributions.

node.text: U.S billionaires have seen their wealth surge by $1.8 trillion during the pandemic. “How will you pay for it!?” is bunk.

node.text: Taxing the rich should not be controversial.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich Elon Musk's $138 billion in pandemic wealth gains could cover the costs of tuition for 5.5 million community college students AND feed 29 million low-income public school kids. After those expenses, Musk would still be $4 billion richer than he was before Covid. Tax the rich.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich … Jeff Bezos' wealth increased by $8.4 billion in *one day* this summer. Meanwhile, our tax code enabled him to pay zero federal income taxes in 2007 AND 2011. The system is rigged for the rich.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich In 1950, the wealthiest Americans paid roughly 70% of their income in taxes, including individual income taxes, corporate taxes, estate taxes, etc. In 2018, their effective tax rate was down to about 25%. Say it with me: Tax the rich.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich Cut taxes on the rich and the money disappears into offshore tax havens. It doesn't trickle down; it surges out. Raise taxes on the rich and the money is invested in infrastructure, education, health care, paid leave, child care, and clean energy. It builds America up.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Robert Reich @RBReich If you think it's time for billionaires to pay their fair share of taxes, urge your members of Congress to support the reconciliation package, which raises taxes on the rich to pay for housing, health care, clean energy investments, and much else. 202-224-3121 Spread the word.'.

Photo by Robert Reich on September 14, 2021. Hello?'.

node.text: Funny enough, Manchin just supported a defense spending increase. But when it comes to investing in people and the planet, that's a bridge too far.
